This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama commemorating the 65th anniversary of the Battle of the Bulge. The proclamation highlights the bravery and sacrifice of American soldiers who fought in the Ardennes Forest region during World War II. It mentions that the Battle of the Bulge was a critical turning point in the war and praises the indomitable strength and determination of the American troops who withstood the German assault. The proclamation also acknowledges the enduring commitment of the US Armed Forces in defending liberty, mentioning ongoing deployments in Iraq and Afghanistan. Obama encourages all Americans to observe the anniversary with appropriate ceremonies and activities.